President Obama has nominated Judge Mark A. Young to serve on the United States District Court for the Central District of California. Judge Young has been serving as a Judge on the Los Angeles Superior Court since 2008, where he handles criminal cases. Prior to his appointment, he worked as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Central District of California from 1998 to 2008. Judge Young has also served as Executive Assistant United States Attorney and Deputy Chief of the Organized Crime Drug Task Force during his time at the United States Attorney's Office. He started his legal career as an associate at the law firm of White & Case LLP. Judge Young received his J.D. from the University of Southern California Gould School of Law in 1995 and his B.A. from the University of California, Los Angeles in 1991.